</div><div type="regularised"><pb facs="#facs_149" id="73v"/><!--The following div is the container for the adress lines of the letter.-->
<div type="addressee">
<ab>Jacob Senften, <expan>pfleg<ex>er</ex></expan> zu Pehemstein</ab>
</div>
<!-- This div contains the letter itselfs. Additions to the text are contained in <add/> elements, struck text in <hi> elements with the attribute 'strikethrough' set to true. -->
<div type="content">
<ab><expan>L<ex>ieber</ex></expan> Jacob, als ir uns
                            <expan>verschr<ex>iben</ex></expan> habt, wie ewch
                                <expan>ankome<ex>n</ex></expan> sey, daz ir in
                            <expan>v<ex>er</ex>dechtnuss</expan> gen uns seyt,
                            <expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> ir geleyts zu uns begert, ewch des zu
                                <expan>v<ex>er</ex>antwten</expan> etc., <add>das
                                    <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir wol
                                <expan>vernom<ex>en</ex></expan></add>. Und wenn ir
                                <expan>hiezwisch<ex>en</ex></expan>
<app>
<note><q type="date">sand Lorenczentag schierist</q>10.08.1420</note>
</app>
<expan>daru<ex>m</ex>b</expan> zu uns <expan>kome<ex>n</ex></expan> wölt, so
                        süllt ir zu uns von uns für uns und die <expan>uns<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
<add>on geverd</add> und bey uns für <expan>all<ex>er</ex>meniklich</expan>
                        iii tag geleyt <expan>hab<ex>e</ex>n</expan>; so
                            <expan>well<ex>e</ex>n</expan> wir ewr red <expan>g<ex>er</ex>n</expan>
                        hören. <expan>Dat<ex>um</ex></expan>
<expan>f<ex>er</ex>ia</expan> iiii<hi rend="sup">a</hi>
<expan>p<ex>ost</ex></expan> Margarete.</ab>
</div>
